REM.description: REM is the base-size of all font-sizes. The default is 16(px), so it relates to 1rem = 16(px). If you change it, it will change all font-related tokens.

universal-scale.description: "universal-scale" is the base-scale of all size-related tokens (size, space, dimension). The default value is 16(px), so it relates to 1rem = 16(px) for font-sizes. If you change it, it will change all size-related tokens, consequently.

none.description: For page gutter / gap between page elements

main-hover.description: Primary background hover color. This acts as the default hover state background color for components with white backgrounds (input dropdown menu items, buttons etc).

solid.description: The darkest background-color used across layouts and components. This switches to surface.soft when in dark mode and is useful for components such as tooltips and WYSIWYG tooltips.

main.description: Foreground color tokens are made to manage all non-text foreground elements in designs across (light/dark) themes, like icons, arrows, etc

main-onbrand.description: Foreground color tokens are made to manage all non-text foreground elements in designs across (light/dark) themes, like icons, arrows, etc

main.description: Text color tokens to manage all text fill colors in designs across (light/dark) themes.

main-onbrand.description: Primary text when used on solid brand color backgrounds. Commonly used for brand theme /primary buttons, for example.

default.description: Background color and blur level for backgrounds that require blurred visuals like pop over overlay.
